## The ritual

This project uses [claude-the-builder](https://github.com/jerryneoneo/claude-the-builder) v{{RITUAL_VERSION}}. Configuration in `ritual.config.yaml`.

```
/plan-init <PRD-PATH>   # one-time: scaffold MASTERPLAN.md from your PRD
/plan-next              # pick the next unblocked task
/build <ID>             # implement on an isolated worktree
/walk <ID>              # human walks through the change (UX prefixes only)
/check <ID>             # quality gates: format, lint, typecheck, test, build
/review <ID>            # independent reviewer subagent against the PRD
/ship <ID>              # squash-merge under a lock; one task = one squash commit
```

Plus orchestrators (`/auto`, `/batch`, `/blitz`), audit (`/doctor`), fast-paths (`/patch`).

### Authoritative sources

- **PRD:** `{{PRD_PATH}}` — read the relevant section before building.
- **Design system:** `{{DESIGN_SYSTEM_PATH}}` — do not invent colors, radii, or components.
- **MASTERPLAN.md** — task index. Per-task source-of-truth is `.taskstate/<ID>.json`.
- **Reviewer rules:** `.claude/ritual/reviewer.project.md` — project non-negotiables.

### Don't

- Bypass hooks (`--no-verify`) — fix the failure
- Use `git add -A` or `git add .` — stage specific files
- Use `--amend` — always create new commits
- Commit on `main` — the `guard-main` hook blocks this; work happens in `.worktrees/<id>/`
- Skip `/walk` for UX tasks — human-in-the-loop is mandatory before gates run

### Do

- Read the PRD section listed in the task's `PRD-refs` column before coding
- Update `.taskstate/<ID>.json` as you progress through the status lattice
- Use the `Task: <ID>` commit trailer (enforced by `/ship`)
- Iterate `/build`-then-`/walk` until visually satisfied before `/check` and `/review`

<!-- ritual:end -->
